title: Namibia elects its first female president in disputed elections
description: Vice-president Netumbo Nandi-Ndaitwah avoids runoff vote, as win extends Swapo party’s 34-year hold on powerNamibia has elected its first female leader, with Netumbo Nandi-Ndaitwah declared the winner of last week’s presidential election in a result that will extend the ruling Swapo party’s 34-year hold on power.Nandi-Ndaitwah, the current vice-president, won with 57% of the vote, according to official results, defying predictions that she might be forced into a runoff. Swapo has ruled the country since its independence from apartheid South Africa in 1990. Continue reading...

title: Joe Biden addresses America’s ‘original sin’ of slavery on Angola visit
description: US president remembers ‘stolen men and women and children brought to our shores’ and lauds American investment in countryJoe Biden addressed America’s history of enslavement in a speech on Tuesday at Angola’s National Museum of Slavery, calling it “our nation’s original sin” during a trip in which he also lauded recent US investment in the region.“We remember the stolen men and women and children who were brought to our shores in chains, subjected to unimaginable cruelty,” Biden said, as the sun set over the water behind him. title: TikTok advertisers stay put after US appeals court upholds law forcing sale
description: A U.S. appeals court upheld a law potentially banning TikTok, but advertisers remain unfazed, maintaining campaigns while preparing backup plans. Rivals like Meta and YouTube stand to gain if TikTok is banned, boosting their stock prices. TikTok's fate now rests with a potential Supreme Court appeal.

title: How UnitedHealthcare CEO Brian Thompson’s killer escaped: From cycle to taxi to bus
description: Police are investigating the fatal shooting of UnitedHealthcare CEO Brian Thompson outside a NYC hotel. The suspect, believed to be a disgruntled employee or client, fled by bus after cycling through Central Park. He arrived from Atlanta on November 24th and used a fake ID at a hostel. The ammunition had the words "deny," "defend," and "depose" written on it.
